<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">2016&nbsp;EVENT&nbsp;FEATURES&nbsp;SEPTEMBER&nbsp;-&nbsp;DECEMBER</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<h4 id="toc32"><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">September 2016:</span></span></h4>
<p><strong>19 September 2016 - International Talk Like a Pirate Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Yarr! Gather 'round, and today listen to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1414765&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="Doctor Cimmerian" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1414765)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/doctor-cimmerian" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1414765); return false;">Doctor Cimmerian</a></span> and Faminepulse's tale of <a href="/scp-2986">a ship in space</a>, the crew of the voyajer, and their adventures.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>25/26 September 2016 - World Dream Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Dreams can inspire us to make wonders of the blank slate that is the future. But what happens when something goes wrong with our sleep-time dreams? Consider the case of <a href="/scp-2245">A Dream's Nightmare</a>, by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/knightknight" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5386562); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=5386562&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="KnightKnight" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=5386562)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/knightknight" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(5386562); return false;">KnightKnight</a></span>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>29 September 2016 - National Coffee Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Whether it's keeping you awake, functioning, sane, or some mix of the three, coffee is a pretty great drink! Just be careful if you're using <a href="/scp-1786">that strange coffee percolator</a> <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drberggren" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1346681); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1346681&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="DrBerggren" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1346681)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drberggren" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1346681); return false;">DrBerggren</a></span> was talking about&#8230;</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc33"><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">October 2016:</span></span></h4>
<p><strong>14 October 2016 - World Egg Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Take a moment today to think of the benefits of eggs. Such as the <strong>MAN EGG</strong> that <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/azzleflux" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1444699); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1444699&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="azzleflux" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1444699)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/azzleflux" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1444699); return false;">azzleflux</a></span> told us about. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">It seems a little questionable.</span> <em>DO NOT LEAVE EGGS OUTSIDE OF A COLD ENVIRONMENT FOR MORE THAN HALF AN HOUR AT A TIME. IF ANYTHING EMERGES FROM YOUR MAN EGG, PLEASE CALL █-███-███-████.</em></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>28 October 2016 - National Chocolate Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Let's celebrate all things chocolate today! Remember to watch out for that one <a href="/scp-743">chocolate fountain</a> by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quikngruvn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(333389); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=333389&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="Quikngruvn" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=333389)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/quikngruvn" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(333389); return false;">Quikngruvn</a></span>, though.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>31 October 2016 - Halloween</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Happy All Hallows' Eve, mortals, enchanters, walkers of the world. Eat candy, spin stories, enjoy the night of fright with friends and folk alike. And, as <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1267048&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="Ihp" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1267048)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/ihp" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1267048); return false;">Ihp</a></span> will tell us of, let us <a href="/dance-the-danse">Dance the Danse</a>!</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc34"><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">November 2016:</span></span></h4>
<p><strong>6 November 2016 - Daylight Saving Time Ends</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>For everyone living in a place that observes DST, it’s time to turn your clocks back! And contemplate the illusion of time, and for those of us who don’t turn the clock at all, some of us might be celebrating <a href="/scp-2098">Saint Simon’s Day</a> with <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mulciber" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(300187); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=300187&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="Mulciber" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=300187)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mulciber" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(300187); return false;">Mulciber</a></span> this year…</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>15 November 2016 - National Clean Out Your Refrigerator Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Hopefully there aren’t any fridges that will fight back when they’re being cleaned today. For those interested in how a fridge can go wrong, <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/azzleflux" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1444699); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1444699&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="azzleflux" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1444699)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/azzleflux" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1444699); return false;">azzleflux</a></span> tells us about <a href="/scp-1731">An Exercise in Futility</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>21 November 2016 - World Hello Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Anyone can participate by verbally greeting ten people today! Think on the importance of communication for peace, and read about <a href="/scp-1281">The Harbinger</a> as <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dreverettmann" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(323946); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=323946&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="DrEverettMann" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=323946)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/dreverettmann" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(323946); return false;">DrEverettMann</a></span> tells us the story of a lonely biomechanical entity with a mission and a message.</li>
</ul>
<h4 id="toc35"><span><span style="text-decoration: underline;">December 2016:</span></span></h4>
<p><strong>13 December 2016 - World Violin Day</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Let us honor the centuries-old string instrument with a tale of a rather curious violin. As <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=301632&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1579869451" alt="Drewbear" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=301632)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drewbear" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(301632); return false;">Drewbear</a></span> tells us, “play it well and keep the life of music flowing”. But is <a href="/scp-1687">the violin</a> really a lost Stradivarius, or rather, something more sinister?</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>24 December 2016 - Christmas Eve</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>'Tis the season! Think back on the 14th Annual Site-19 Senior Staff Christmas Eve Caroling, at the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/december-24th-2011-hub">December 24th, 2011 Hub</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>31 December 2016 - New Year's Eve</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Another year has come to an end. Let us think of the <a href="/quiet-days">Quiet Days</a>, and what we have experienced, as we look towards the future.</li>
</ul>
</div>
